  "elapsed_s": 220.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in the same fashion, you can just imagine yourself being a non-Jew and suddenly watch a Jew with his kaftan and tallis around his neck and a shtreimel on a Saturday-- what a strange apparition that was for him.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So even where there was no animus-- and there was plenty of that, certainly among the gentry.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The gentry felt itself, I, I would say, displaced by the Jews, and demanded to take the place of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Prior to 1939, did you ever personally feel that you were in physical danger at any time?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, actually, I was in physical danger as a-- as a student in the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] elementary school.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At times, a, a-- our teacher would keep the few Jews that went to the government school, like myself, during the pauses that we used to have between every hour for about 10 minutes or so.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He would consider it the better part of wisdom to keep us in the classroom.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because if we went outside, we were bound to clash with the, oh, you know, 99% of the non-Jewish students who, you know, needed really no cause to pick a fight and to bloody our noses.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, it, it, it did.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course it did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I hope you have several years available.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My father, whose name in Hungarian was Menyheart, M-E-N-Y-H-E-A-R-T, and-- but whose Hebrew and Yiddish names were Menachem Mendel, was, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I would say, a, a well-known personality in, in Hungary and beyond.",
      "word_count": 40
    }
  ],
